July 15 (Reuters) - The following corporate finance-related stories were reported by media:

* Indonesia's Lion Air Group is in talks with Qantas Airways Ltd <QAN.AX> about buying the Australian carrier's stake in the Singapore-based affiliate of its budget airline Jetstar, a person familiar with the matter told Reuters. [ID:nL4N0PP2WU]  * Privately held U.S. billboard company Van Wagner, which owns billboards in New York's Times Square and on buses on the Las Vegas strip, is exploring a sale that could fetch more than $600 million, people familiar with the matter said. [ID:nL2N0PP22G]  For the deals of the day click on [DEALS/]